  "prompt": "I just got friendzoned. What should I do now?",
  "response": "Getting friendzoned can be disheartening, but it\u2019s not the end of the world. Here are a few steps to help you navigate this situation:\n\n1. **Accept Their Decision:** Respect their feelings and accept their decision gracefully. It\u2019s important to recognize that everyone has their own preferences and emotional boundaries.\n\n2. **Take Some Time:** Give yourself some time to process your emotions. Feeling hurt is natural, and taking a step back can help you gain perspective.\n\n3. **Evaluate the Friendship:** Consider whether you\u2019re comfortable being friends with this person or if you need some distance. Maintaining a friendship is possible, but only if you can genuinely accept the platonic relationship without hidden hopes or resentment.\n\n4. **Stay Busy and Focus on Yourself:** Engage in activities you enjoy, focus on your hobbies, and spend time with other friends. Keeping yourself occupied can help divert your mind from the situation.\n\n5. **Meet New People:** Expanding your social circle can introduce you to new individuals and potential romantic interests. It\u2019s an opportunity to form connections with others who may reciprocate your feelings.\n\n6. **Reflect on What You Want:** Think about what you\u2019re seeking in a relationship and whether you\u2019re ready for one. Use this time to grow and understand your own desires better.\n\n7. **Communicate Openly:** If you decide to keep the friendship, communicate openly and honestly with your friend about your feelings and boundaries. It will help prevent misunderstandings and ensure both of you are on the same page.\n\n8. **Stay Positive:** Remember that rejection is a part of life and doesn\u2019t define your worth. Stay positive and keep an open mind towards future opportunities.\n\nUltimately, the key to moving forward is to respect both your feelings and theirs while focusing on your personal growth and happiness.",
